claims:
Claims What is Claimed: 1. A first node comprising, a processor, a memory, and communication circuitry, the first node configured to connect to a network via the communication circuitry, the first node comprising computer-executable instructions stored in the memory of the first node which, when executed by the processor of the first node, perform operations comprising: determining a network configuration comprising a chain of nodes from the first node, through a second node, to a destination node; based on physical and cyber security attributes associated with the second node, obtaining a security posture value associated with the second node, receiving a data packet; obtaining a security posture level requirement associated with the data packet; determining whether to forward the data packet to the second node, based on the security posture value associated with the second node; and forwarding the data packet to the second node when the security posture value is sufficient relative to the security posture level requirement associated with the data packet. 2. The first node as recited in claim 1, wherein determining the network configuration further comprises identifying one or more network paths for incoming data packets across a service function chain. 3. The first node as recited in any one of the preceding claims, wherein the security posture value provides a trust metric corresponding to an overall level of trust in the second node. 4. The first node as recited in any one of the preceding claims, wherein determining whether to forward the data packet to the second node comprises: determining a plurality of next hops from the first node that are sufficient relative to the security posture level requirement associated with the data packet; and identifying the second node as one of the plurality of next hops. 5. The first node as recited in any one of the preceding claims, wherein determining whether to forward the data packet to the second node comprises: extracting a network services header from the data packet; 

 identifying the security posture level requirement in the network services header; and determining whether the security posture value associated with the second node is equal to or greater than the security posture level requirement associated with the data packet. 6. The first node as recited in any one of the preceding claims, wherein the security posture value is also derived based on policies of at least one stakeholder service provider entity. 7. The first node as recited in any one of the preceding claims, wherein the security posture value is also derived based on policies of a plurality of stakeholder service provider entities. 8. The first node as recited in any one of the preceding claims, wherein the first and second nodes are network functions within a network slice. 9. The first node as recited in claim 1, wherein the first and second nodes are virtualized network functions. 10. The first node as recited in any one of the preceding claims, wherein the network is a network slice comprising a plurality of network functions. 11. The first node as recited in claim 1, wherein the first node comprises an independent trusted entity. 12. The first node as recited in any one of the preceding claims, wherein the physical and cyber security attributes associated with the second node are exposed to enable the first node to derive the security posture value based on the physical and cyber security attributes. 13. The first node as recited in any one of the preceding claims, wherein the physical and cyber security attributes associated with the second node are based on an evaluation performed by a plurality of independent trusted evaluation entities. 14. An apparatus comprising, a processor, a memory, and communication circuitry, the apparatus configured to connect to a network via the communication circuitry, the apparatus 

 comprising computer-executable instructions stored in the memory of the apparatus which, when executed by the processor of the apparatus, perform operations comprising: determining an aggregate security posture value associated with the network; determining a required security posture level associated with the apparatus; and determining whether to access a service provided by the network based on comparing the aggregate security posture value with the required security posture level; and when the aggregate security posture value is sufficient as compared to the aggregate security posture value, accessing the service provided by the network. 15. The apparatus as recited in claim 14, wherein the required security posture level is obtained from a Service Description Document. 16. The apparatus as recited in claim 14, wherein the aggregate security posture value indicates a trust metric corresponding to an overall level of trust in the network. 17. The apparatus as recited in claim 14, wherein the aggregate security posture value is determined based on policies of at least one stakeholder service provider entity. 18. The apparatus as recited in claim 14, wherein the aggregate security posture value is determined derived based on policies of a plurality of stakeholder service provider entities.
